parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Brake Hydraulic Control Unit (HCU) can cause the brake pedal to become soft or hard, leading to reduced braking power, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down
the ABS light illuminates
and the service brake system warning light appears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or slips when shifting gears
the transmission fails to engage
the vehicle stalls or loses power
and unusual noises or vibrations are present.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shut-off of the engine can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off without warning
the vehicle loses power
and the "wrench" or "check engine" light may illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause accidents or injuries, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop
and unusual noises or vibrations are present.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The gas pedal sticks or becomes stuck
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the accelerator pedal fails to respond
the vehicle jerks or surges forward
and the engine warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking accelerator pedal can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The gas pedal sticks or becomes stuck
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the accelerator pedal fails to respond

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents or loss of control, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without warning
the gas pedal sticks or becomes stuck

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Shock Tower and Mount Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear shock tower and mount can cause the shock absorber to detach from the vehicle, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Loud banging or thumping noise from the rear of the vehicle
rust or corrosion on the rear wheel wells
shock absorber detaching from the vehicle
and loss of control while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Rear Subframe and Suspension Components
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the rear subframe and suspension components can cause the vehicle to become inoperable and lead to loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Rust or corrosion on the rear subframe
suspension components
and wheel wells
grinding noise during left turns
and loss of traction control and ABS systems.
